This works great, hate the touch remote that comes with player

Easy to set up with good on screen instructions.  Panasonic's remote app is a dud, but this one works.  No control delays and quick to start up.  Can even use voice commands for many things including going to Netflix (which is under extras if you don't want to use voice).  My only suggestion is to add that same functionality for other internet apps (especially Pandora) including a shortcut just for "internet" like is on the actual remote to take you to all of your internet apps.  Or just add a button for Netflix, Pandora and Internet apps in general.  I use the internet apps by far the most on my player so a quicker shortcut and a voice shortcut to them would be a major boon to this app for me.  **Note that you can get to them with this app, it just takes a couple more clicks than if they were added under extras and/or had dedicated buttons or voice access**
Awesome app even uses voice commands to control the player
the keyboard doesn't work for the s3 you might want to look into that. and also the eject button doesn't work? thanks
replyContent: The keyboard should now be fixed. Please contact me via the support email address if you are still having problems with eject.

Works very well with bdt215. Great app. When Google switched over to play store my paid version kept acting like it was an expired trial. I contacted the author and after a timely response with a few troubleshooting options to try, I am back to using it again. I think he spent more than the $2.50 or whatever I spent on this app in his own time helping me fix a problem that his app didn't even cause.  I know this is a niche app but I really respect that in anyone that sells a product, especially nowadays.
Works great.  To bad Panasonic couldn't do something like this for their own equipment.

Not perfect but definitely worth the money.  Easy to set up. Only complaint is too many options so have to move between screens more than I would like. That's probably inevitable though given the number of machines it works with. Overall very good.
With two little kids, remotes tend to get misplaced quite a bit, so this has saved a lot of frustration, and even helped avert a few tantrums.

Works exactly as promised. I had a minor network issue specific to my security settings but quickly solved the problem with the help of the developer. App feels more responsive than my dedicated remote.
